It is an independent TypeScript implementation whose tool, resource, and prompt
interface is designed to be compatible with the uk-legal-mcp project. It was
written against the Model Context Protocol TypeScript SDK
(@modelcontextprotocol/sdk) and is not derived from uk-legal-mcp's source code.
It targets publicly available UK legal data sources (The National Archives Find
Case Law, legislation.gov.uk, the UK Parliament APIs, and GOV.UK/HMRC); those
sources and their data are the property of their respective owners and are used
under their own terms.

Third-party open-source packages used at runtime (declared in package.json)
remain under their own licences, held in each package's distribution.


